gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 89, Timberwolves 88
gameRecap.excerpt: The Clippers defeated the Timberwolves, 89-88. Kawhi Leonard led all scorers with 32 points (12-26 FG) and five rebounds for the Clippers, while Norman Powell added 24 points (6-8 3PT FG) in the victory. Anthony Edwards tallied 27 points, five rebounds and three steals for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Clippers have won back-to-back games as they improve to 39-20 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 42-19.
